The paper focuses on improving information-seeking dialogue systems through the analysis of conversational transcripts. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and human-computer interaction (HCI), which are covered by cs.CL and cs.HC respectively. The use of process mining techniques to analyze the structure of interaction processes suggests a focus on data-driven approaches, which aligns with the sub-categories of cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed model across multiple datasets suggests a focus on information retrieval (IR), which is covered by cs.IR.
